main event: On three occasions in January and February 1956, a bright, slow-moving object resembling a flying saucer was seen over Harrisonville, Missouri. The object circled Harrisonville on the last sighting before disappearing to the east.
interesting points: The witness reported seeing the object three times over a span of three weeks, describing it as very bright and moving slowly.
The object disappeared to the north on the first occasion and made a circular pattern over Harrisonville on the last sighting before disappearing to the east.
The reporting officer suggested that what the witness saw were probably conventional or jet aircraft, due to the high number of such aircraft operating in the vicinity.
The witness expressed concern after seeing the object multiple times, prompting them to report it to authorities.
